<section id="career">
  <h2>Career &amp; Strengths</h2>
  <p>The Rooster's combination of meticulous observation, courage, and tireless work ethic makes them naturally suited to careers that demand precision, integrity, and the willingness to hold high standards.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Military &amp; Defence</strong> — Discipline, punctuality, and courage under pressure are Rooster hallmarks</li>
    <li><strong>Journalism &amp; Investigation</strong> — The sharp eye for detail and commitment to truth that investigative work demands</li>
    <li><strong>Accounting &amp; Auditing</strong> — Meticulous precision and the integrity to report exactly what the numbers show</li>
    <li><strong>Performing Arts &amp; Fashion</strong> — The Rooster's flair for presentation and their eye for visual detail</li>
    <li><strong>Surgery &amp; Precision Medicine</strong> — Steady hands guided by exacting standards and careful observation</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section id="culture">
  <h2>Cultural Significance</h2>
  <p>The Rooster is celebrated in Chinese culture as a symbol of <strong>punctuality, vigilance, and the triumph of light over darkness</strong>. The rooster's crow at dawn was understood as the sound that banishes evil spirits and ghosts — in the <em>Chunqiu Fanlu</em> (春秋繁露, Luxuriant Dew of the Spring and Autumn Annals), Dong Zhongshu describes the rooster's cry as a cosmic signal that restores yang energy and dispels the yin forces of night.</p>
  <p>Images of roosters were traditionally placed on doors and walls as protective talismans, particularly at Chinese New Year. The word for rooster (雞, jī) is a homophone of "auspicious" (吉, jí) in many Chinese dialects, making rooster imagery a popular symbol in decorative arts. The elaborate plumage of the rooster also connects it to Chinese ideals of beauty and self-presentation — the phrase "鶴立雞群" (a crane among roosters) describes someone who stands out from the crowd, but the idiom acknowledges the Rooster's own impressive bearing as the baseline for comparison.</p>
</section>
